Definition.WordDefinition:
Archery \Arch"er*y\, n. [OE. archerie.] 1. The use of the bow and arrows in battle, hunting, etc.; the art, practice, or skill of shooting with a bow and arrows. [1913 Webster]
2. Archers, or bowmen, collectively. [1913 Webster]
Let all our archery fall off In wings of shot a-both sides of the van. --Webster (1607). [1913 Webster]
archery n : the sport of shooting arrows with a bow
